<h4>
	Important Information for our guests:</h4>
<ul class="listing_1" style="padding-right: 8px;">
	<li>
		Please bring your log book and diving certification card</li>
	<li>
		Medical check is recommended but not obligatory</li>
	<li>
		The first dive is a check dive at same time - obligatory for all divers.</li>
	<li>
		Dives are guided by Instructor and dive guide</li>
	<li>
		Experienced divers can dive on their own - after check dive</li>
	<li>
		Equipment and compressor stay on the Dhoni throughout the safari. That means there is no carrying heavy equipment and no compressor noise on the mother ship. First aid box and oxygen are onboard.</li>
	<li>
		Dives are performed according Maldivian law and Padi standards - no decompression dives, buddy system, maximum depth is 100 Feet for AOWD or equivalent, for OWD or equivalent certified divers 59 Feet maximum (according Maldivian diving regulation).</li>
	<li>
		last dive 24h before flight back</li>
	<li>
		use of diving computer/person is obligatory</li>
	<li>
		English is board language</li>
	<li>
		DAN diving insurance ( valid max. 21 days) for &euro; 10 bookable on board</li>
	<li>
		20 dives are offered during a 7 night safari and 40 dives are offered during a 14 night safari</li>
</ul>
<h4>
	Required diving certification/skills</h4>
<p>
	<img alt="" class="imgoffer" height="168" src="images/div_certi.jpg" style="margin: 10px 0px 10px 10px; clear: right;" width="235" /></p>
<p>
	You need at least a Padi Open Water Diver or an equivalent certificate to join one of our diving cruises. This basic certificate allows you to dive to a maximum of 59 Feet.<br />
	<br />
	In order to be well-prepared for the challenging diving conditions in the Maldives and to be able to dive below 59 Feet (where many of the highlights are) we recommend doing the Padi Advanced Open Water or an equivalent certificate before or during your cruise. Divers who have not dived in a while can do a Padi Scuba Review course to refresh their diving skills.<br />
	<br />
	During the check dive, the dive guide will evaluate the skill levels of all divers. The diving conditions in the Maldives are challenging and if the dive guide or a guest feel that it is necessary, guided dives for individuals can be arranged for USD 10 per dive. Guided dives provide an opportunity to get used to diving in strong currents, entering and exiting the water from a dive tender (Dhoni) and doing fast descents under the supervision of an experienced dive master. We recommend guided dives to all divers with little open sea, current and liveaboard diving experience. In most cases, diver(s) only need a couple of guided dives at the beginning before diving with the group for the rest of their stay</p>
<h4>
	Dhoni</h4>
<p>
	All dives are done from an extra diving boat (58 Feet). Equipment and compressor stay on the Dhoni throughout the safari. That means there is no carrying heavy equipment and no compressor noise on the mother ship. First aid box and oxygen are onboard.</p>
<h4>
	Diving Equipment</h4>
<p>
	In case you wish to rent diving equipment - Please pre-order rental equipment! Rental equipment prices are subject for change without further notice.</p>        </div>

<script>

	  // When the document loads do everything inside here ...
	  $(document).ready(function(){

		// When a link is clicked
		$("a.tab").click(function () {


			// switch all tabs off
			$(".current").removeClass("current");

			// switch this tab on
			$(this).addClass("current");

			// slide all content up
			$(".content_text").slideUp();

			// slide this content up
			var content_show = $(this).attr("name");
			$("#"+content_show).slideDown();

		});

	  });
  </script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#tourcharge').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
   $.ajax({
   type: "POST",
   url: "submitliveboardenquiry.php",
   data: str,
   success: function(msg)
   {
		$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings){
		var myList = msg.split("||");	
					$(this).html(myList[0])
					$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						//$('#submitBtn').attr('disabled',true);
						//alert('test');
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
});

}

 });

return false;

}
</script>

      <div class="resortbox tabbed_area" >
        <h1>Sting Ray Liveaboard</h1>
        <ul>
          		  <li><a  name="idTab1"  class="tab current">Overview</a></li>
		  		  
		  		             <li ><a name="idTab7" class="tab" >Diving Info</a></li>
		 
		  		  		  
		   		  
		   		 <li><a name="idTab3" class="tab"> The Routes</a></li>

	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab1">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		  
			  			  			  
        
        
		<div id="fb-root">
	&nbsp;</div>
<script src="http://connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1"></script><p>
	<fb:like-box header="false" href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Maldives-Traveller/149004041802679" show_faces="false" stream="false" width="280"></fb:like-box></p>
<p>
	<strong>Sting Ray Liveaboard </strong><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">is a liveaboard built for divers. The boat length of 110 ft. Boat is conveniently design to carter to the dive market. We have a reputation of running successful tours for more then a decade and is well known among the dive community for its reasonable scuba dive holiday package to Maldives. The service provided by Sting Ray is more then what you ask for the reasonable price which you book the holiday package.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">Crew &ndash; have 10 to 12 crew onboard who have been working in this field passionately for years.</span></p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">Dive Guides &ndash; &nbsp;Minimum 2 dive guides always onboard , dive guides are highly expereinced and diving with Sting Ray for the past 3 years . Our guides are &nbsp;professionals from Maldives.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>
	The Chef &ndash; The chef prepares cuisine unparalleled and diversified, flavours from the Maldives , East and the west. sure to please all, and their fresh sashimi is always a cruise highlight!</p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold; ">Boat Specification</span></p>
<ul boat_.gif="" class="boatfeature" images="" no-repeat="" right="" scroll="" style="" top="">
	<li>
		Type:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Designed specializing to the dive Market to Maldives.</li>
	<li>
		Year Built :</li>
	<li class="feature">
		2001</li>
	<li>
		Hull:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Wooden, Double Deck</li>
	<li>
		Length:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		100 foot / 30 meters</li>
	<li>
		Beam:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		27 feet / 8.75 meters</li>
	<li>
		Accommodation:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Maximum 18 passengers (with 4 tripple rooms)</li>
	<li>
		No of Cabins:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		9 double bed cabins, Hot &amp; Cold water, Air conditioning, Specious 10ft x 12ft area carpeted room</li>
	<li>
		Main Saloon</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Full Space Dinning Hall / Buffet Style, Lounge with Sofas, Full service Bar</li>
	<li>
		Entertainments:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Hi-Fi, TV, VCR, DVD, Library and Table Games</li>
	<li>
		Engine:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Yamaha Diesel Motor 278 BHP, Cruising Speed 10 knots / hrs</li>
	<li>
		Electricity:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		220 volts A/C, 12/24 volts DC</li>
	<li>
		Diving:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Medical Oxygen with required Accessories, Dan Oxygen Kit on the Dive Tender, Medical Lockers on Board, Air Compressor main unit type Bauer Marina 320 &amp; Coltri MCH 16 Tropical Plus, 7 Tanks Aluminum 92 cubic ft/15 liters, 18 Tanks Aluminum 82 cubic ft/12liters</li>
	<li>
		Communication:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		VHF Radios/GPS Chart Plotter/Depth Sounder/Cell Phones/Small fiber speed launch 25 hp to visit Island</li>
	<li>
		Crew On Board:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		10-12 crews on board who are highly Experience on field.</li>
</ul>		  </div>

	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab3">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		<p>
	&nbsp;The Routes vary depending on the number of nights within the tour. Mostly we have 7 nights tour which we will be able to cover the most best dive sites of Maldives within the range of Male&#39; Atoll &amp; Ari Atoll. We also do longer tour routes of 9 nights or longer then 9 nights depending on the request of the clients .</p>
<p>
	Within 9 nights we will be able to travel further and cover Vaavu , and Rasdhu Atoll range. Our most recommended length of the tour is a 9 day tour as this tour can cover most of the best dives sites.</p>
<p>
	There are few Uniq tours of 14 days which travel to Huvadhu Atoll Tour , which is a remarkable tour as to its long voyage and the remote area where very few liveaboards will travel to cover such a long range and dive the most un destructed dive sites in Maldives</p>
<p>
	The routes are planned in advance however it is not fixed as the best diving points in Maldives can vary depending on the current and visibility and depending on overall weather. Our Dive guides will select the best choice of route and dive site for the liveaboard tour. &nbsp;</p>		  </div>

		  <div style="width:620px;">
		  <h4>
	Payment &amp; Cancellation Policies</h4>
<ul class="listing_1">
	<li>
		On Confirmation Of Booking Advance deposit of 50% of total invoiced amount is required. 25% of the amount is non refundable in case of cancellation after confirmation</li>
	<li>
		Remaining Balance should be settled 55 days before the departure date of the tour.</li>
	<li>
		Cancellation received less then 49 days for the departure of the tour, full invoiced amount will be charged.</li>
	<li>
		Late Booking inquiry less the 60 days of departure date will be required to do full payment.</li>
	<li>
		All cancellation is required to be informed by written document (e-mail )</li>
</ul>		  </div>

	 <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab7">
        <div class="boxcontent">
		<p>
	Pricing Price include:</p>
<p>
	Accommodation in air conditioned cabins with outside window, ensuite shower (hot water) and toilet, towels and room service.&nbsp;<br />
	Full board meals, Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner buffet style.<br />
	Cooled water, Tea and coffee available 24h.<br />
	Up to 3 guided dives per day including one night dive per week.<br />
	Tanks: 12 lt Aluminium DIN/INT, lead belts, security balloon, extra diving boat, instructor and dive guide (PADI). Use of fishing gear- local style, including hook, fishing line, weight and baits.<br />
	Island hopping, snorkeling service and picknick on uninhabited island.<br />
	Male visit (sightseeing and shopping in Maldives capital) is offered on last day evening. Airport Meet and Greet, transfers to and from the boat.</p>
<p>
	MINIMUM OCCUPATION TO START SAFARI</p>
<p>
	May-Dec: at least 8 guests&nbsp;<br />
	Dec-May: at least 6 guests<br />
	<br />
	DIVING RENTAL EQUIPMENT<br />
	<br />
	Please inform us in advance if you need any dive gear for rent.<br />
	<br />
	The rental prices are:<br />
	<br />
	BCD + Regulator: US$ 25 / day<br />
	ABC Set: US$ 10 / day<br />
	Diving computer US$ 10 per day<br />
	UW Torch US$ 5 /dive<br />
	DRINKS Draft beer: US$ 3<br />
	Mineral Water: US$ 2.50<br />
	Soft Drinks: US$ 2<br />
	Fresh Fruit Juice: US$3 International wines and cocktails available &nbsp;</p>        </div>

<script>

	  // When the document loads do everything inside here ...
	  $(document).ready(function(){

		// When a link is clicked
		$("a.tab").click(function () {


			// switch all tabs off
			$(".current").removeClass("current");

			// switch this tab on
			$(this).addClass("current");

			// slide all content up
			$(".content_text").slideUp();

			// slide this content up
			var content_show = $(this).attr("name");
			$("#"+content_show).slideDown();

		});

	  });
  </script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.form.js"></script>  
<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#tourcharge').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
   $.ajax({
   type: "POST",
   url: "submitliveboardenquiry.php",
   data: str,
   success: function(msg)
   {
		$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings){
		var myList = msg.split("||");	
					$(this).html(myList[0])
					$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						//$('#submitBtn').attr('disabled',true);
						//alert('test');
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
});

}

 });

return false;

}
</script>

        <h1>Maavahi Liveaboard</h1>
        <ul>
          		  <li><a  name="idTab1"  class="tab current">Overview</a></li>
		  		  
		  		             <li ><a name="idTab7" class="tab" >Diving Info</a></li>

	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab1">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		  
			  			  <div class="galleryframe"><div class="thumbs1"><a href="manager/uploads/images/710.jpg"  title="Maavahi Liveaboard"><img src="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/displayimage.php?image=http://www.maldivestraveller.com/manager/uploads/images/710.jpg&width=271&height=180&color=16a942&quality=100&resizeImage=0&nocache=1" alt="Maavahi Liveaboard" /></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/711.jpg"  title="Maavahi Safari Maldives"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/712.jpg"  title="Maavahi Dive Liveaboard Sundeck"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/713.jpg"  title="Liveaboard Maavahi Sand Bank"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/714.jpg"  title="Maavahi Safari Liveaboard Cabin"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/715.jpg"  title="Maavahi Dinning Area"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/716.jpg"  title="Maavahi Outdoor relaxing"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/717.jpg"  title="Maavahi Cabin Toilets"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/718.jpg"  title="Maavahi Top Deck Wheel House"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/719.jpg"  title="Maavahi cabin walk way"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/720.jpg"  title="Maavahi Liveaboard Bar"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/721.jpg"  title="Maavahi Liveaboard Dinning"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/722.jpg"  title="Maavahi Liveaboard Crew Team"></a></div><p style='text-align:center;'><a href='javascript:void(0)' id='viewgallery'>View Gallery</a></p></div>			  
        
        
		<p>
	Maavahi Liveaboard An exclusive liveaboard specialized in many years of diving operation in Maldives for ocean lovers. One of the well reputed liveaboard for its steady and quality tours provided .</p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;">Maavahi Liveaboard is a boat build by local craftsmen and engineers with the modern amenities to set the standard for traveler and adventures who love to scuba dive in Maldives. The boat had its first maiden voyage in 1998. The boat has a well reputation among its repeat customers and the dive Market.<br />
	Maavahi is 25.91 m (85 ft) long and 8.23 m (27 ft) wide. It has three decks and eight beautiful and well-furnished cabins: 7 twins and 1 double.<br />
	</span><br />
	Diving &ndash; Maavahi is well reputed for its dive operation over the years. We maintain our quality and arrange the best route depending on the season and the ocean current as well other factors we consider before making a trip.<br />
	<br />
	Accommodation &ndash; there are 8 cabins well furnished. 4 cabins comes with 1 double bed and 1 single bed at the top and 3 cabins with twin beds (1 below and 1 above). Seven cabins are located on the first deck and 1 double cabin is located on the second deck. All cabins have air-conditioning, an attached toilet, limited wardrobe facilities and a DC wall fan&#8232;&#8232;<br />
	<br />
	Dining: The well-lit and exceptionally beautiful and spacious dining room with its beautiful wooden ceiling is also located on the second deck. In the front, adjoining the main restaurant is an outdoor restaurant offering a unique opportunity to dine in the open and in full view of the beautiful surrounding. Enjoy the delicious meals, the unmatched hospitality and service of our crew...</p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold; "><br />
	Boat Specification</span></span></p>
<ul boat_.gif="" class="boatfeature" images="" no-repeat="" right="" scroll="" style="" top="">
	<li>
		Type:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Wooden Design specializing in Maldives liveaboard diving tours.</li>
	<li>
		Year Built :</li>
	<li class="feature">
		1998</li>
	<li>
		Refurbished :</li>
	<li class="feature">
		2010</li>

		27 meters / 30 meters</li>
	<li>
		Beam:</li>

		27 feet / 8.75 meters</li>
	<li>
		Accommodation:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Maximum 16 passengers&nbsp;</li>
	<li>
		No of Cabins:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		5 cabins with double bed and 1 single bed above. 3 cabins with twin beds. &nbsp;Hot &amp; Cold water, Air conditioning</li>
	<li>
		Main Saloon</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Full Space Dinning Hall / Buffet Style, Our door dinning, Full service Bar</li>
	<li>

	<li>
		Communication:</li>

	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab3">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		<p>
	&nbsp;The Routes vary depending on the number of nights within the tour. Mostly we have 7 nights tour which we will be able to cover the most best dive sites of Maldives within the range of Male&#39; Atoll &amp; Ari Atoll. We also do longer tour routes of 9 nights or longer then 9 nights depending on the request of the clients .</p>
<p>
	Within 9 nights we will be able to travel further and cover Vaavu , and Rasdhu Atoll range. Our most recommended length of the tour is a 9 day tour as this tour can cover most of the best dives sites.</p>
<p>
	There are few Unique tours of 14 days which travel to Huvadhu Atoll Tour , which is a remarkable tour as to its long voyage and the remote area where very few liveaboards will travel to cover such a long range and dive the most breathtaking dive sites in Maldives</p>
<p>
	The routes are planned in advance however it is not fixed as the best diving points in Maldives can vary depending on the current and visibility and depending on overall weather. Our Dive guides will select the best choice of route and dive site for the liveaboard tour. &nbsp;</p>		  </div>

		<p>
	Pricing Price include:</p>
<p>
	Accommodation in air conditioned cabins with outside window, ensuite shower (hot water) and toilet, towels and room service.&nbsp;<br />
	Full board meals, Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner buffet style.<br />
	Cooled water, Tea and coffee available 24h.<br />
	Up to 3 guided dives per day including one night dive per week.<br />
	Tanks: 12 lt Aluminium DIN/INT, lead belts, security balloon, extra diving boat, instructor and dive guide (PADI). Use of fishing gear- local style, including hook, fishing line, weight and baits.<br />
	Island hopping, snorkeling service and picknick on uninhabited island.<br />
	Male visit (sightseeing and shopping in Maldives capital) is offered on last day evening. Airport Meet and Greet, transfers to and from the boat.</p>
<p>
	MINIMUM OCCUPATION TO START SAFARI</p>
<p>
	May-Dec: at least 8 guests&nbsp;<br />
	Dec-May: at least 6 guests<br />

<script>

	  // When the document loads do everything inside here ...
	  $(document).ready(function(){

		// When a link is clicked
		$("a.tab").click(function () {


			// switch all tabs off
			$(".current").removeClass("current");

			// switch this tab on
			$(this).addClass("current");

			// slide all content up
			$(".content_text").slideUp();

			// slide this content up
			var content_show = $(this).attr("name");
			$("#"+content_show).slideDown();

		});

	  });
  </script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.form.js"></script>  
<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#tourcharge').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
   $.ajax({
   type: "POST",
   url: "submitliveboardenquiry.php",
   data: str,
   success: function(msg)
   {
		$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings){
		var myList = msg.split("||");	
					$(this).html(myList[0])
					$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						//$('#submitBtn').attr('disabled',true);
						//alert('test');
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
});

}

 });

return false;

}
</script>

    <div class="body_content">
      <div class="resortbox tabbed_area" >
        <h1>Southern Cross</h1>
        <ul>
          		  <li><a  name="idTab1"  class="tab current">Overview</a></li>
		  		  
		  		             <li ><a name="idTab7" class="tab" >Diving Info</a></li>
		 
		  		  		  
		   		  
		   		 <li><a name="idTab3" class="tab"> The Routes</a></li>
		  		  
		              
         
          <li><a name="idTab6" class="tab">Schedules</a></li>
		   <li><a name="idTab8" class="tab">Reviews</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <br class="spacer" />
	 
		
		


      
	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab1">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		  
			  			  <div class="galleryframe"><div class="thumbs1"><a href="manager/uploads/images/698.jpg"  title="Southern Cross Maldives Liveaboard"><img src="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/displayimage.php?image=http://www.maldivestraveller.com/manager/uploads/images/698.jpg&width=271&height=180&color=16a942&quality=100&resizeImage=0&nocache=1" alt="Southern Cross Maldives Liveaboard" /></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/699.jpg"  title="Kasimo Wreck Maldives Dive Tour"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/701.jpg"  title="Southern Cross Lobby Maldives Liveaboard"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/702.jpg"  title="Southern Cross Lobby Maldives Liveaboard"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/703.jpg"  title="Southern Cross Cabin Maldives Liveaboard"></a></div><p style='text-align:center;'><a href='javascript:void(0)' id='viewgallery'>View Gallery</a></p></div>			  
        
        
		<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold; ">Over View:</span></p>
<p>
	Southern cross one of the finest mid range liveaboard operated for diving in Maldives. Southern cross can accommodate a maximum of 22 divers. The boat consists of 10 cabins with all modern amenities. All rooms are full air-condition and with en suites. The cabins have comfortable large toilets with separate shower cabins with hot and cold water.</p>
<p>
	Southern cross liveaboard is one of the spacious and well-facilitated boat for all dive lovers who is interested in doing Maldives Liveaboard tours. The boat is fully equipped with the modern dive compressors nitrox and all other well facilitated specializing in diving.</p>
<p>
	Other then the main factor of diving , Boat is also very spacious and have a whirl pool for fun time and relaxing other then diving.</p>
<h4>
	Boat Spec</h4>
<ul boat_.gif="" class="boatfeature" images="" no-repeat="" right="" scroll="" style="" top="">
	<li>
		Type:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Live Aboard designed for convenience of Dive Travelers</li>
	<li>
		Year Built :</li>
	<li class="feature">
		November 2007</li>
	<li>
		Hull:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Wooden, Double Deck</li>
	<li>
		Length:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		35 meters</li>
	<li>
		Beam:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		10 meters</li>
	<li>
		Accommodation:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Maximum 22 passengers</li>
	<li>
		No of Cabins:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		10 (all cabins with en suites) Hot &amp; Cold water, Air conditioning, Specious &amp; luxurious.</li>
	<li>
		Main Saloon</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Full Space Dinning Hall / Buffet Style, Lounge with Sofas, Full service Bar</li>
	<li>
		Entertainments:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Hi-Fi, TV, VCR, DVD, Library and Table Games</li>
	<li>
		Engine:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Cummins 425 HP engine diesel</li>
	<li>
		Electricity:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		02 Onan gen sets 35 KW soundproof</li>
	<li>
		Communication:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		VHF Radios/GPS Chart Plotter/Depth Sounder/Cell Phones/Small fiber speed launch 25 hp to visit Island</li>
	<li>
		Crew On Board:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		8-12 crews on board who have had over 8 to 10 years of Experience on field. Dive Master have over 10 years experience.</li>
</ul>		  </div>

	    <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab2">
          <div class="boxcontent">
				  </div>
		    <br  class="spacer" />
           <img src="images/spacer.gif" alt="" height="12" />
       
      </div>
	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab3">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		<p>
	&nbsp;The Routes vary depending on the number of nights within the tour. Mostly we have 7 nights tour which we will be able to cover the most best dive sites of Maldives within the range of Male&#39; Atoll &amp; Ari Atoll. We also do longer tour routes of 9 nights or longer then 9 nights depending on the request of the clients .</p>
<p>
	Within 9 nights we will be able to travel further and cover Vaavu , and Rasdhu Atoll range. Our most recommended length of the tour is a 9 day tour as this tour can cover most of the best dives sites.</p>
<p>
	There are few Uniq tours of 14 days which travel to Huvadhu Atoll Tour , which is a remarkable tour as to its long voyage and the remote area where very few liveaboards will travel to cover such a long range and dive the most un destructed dive sites in Maldives</p>
<p>
	The routes are planned in advance however it is not fixed as the best diving points in Maldives can vary depending on the current and visibility and depending on overall weather. Our Dive guides will select the best choice of route and dive site for the liveaboard tour. &nbsp;</p>		  </div>

		  <h4>
	Payment &amp; Cancellation Policies</h4>
<ul class="listing_1">
	<li>
		On Confirmation Of Booking Advance deposit of 50% of total invoiced amount is required. 25% of the amount is non refundable in case of cancellation after confirmation</li>
	<li>
		Remaining Balance should be settled 55 days before the departure date of the tour.</li>
	<li>
		Cancellation received less then 49 days for the departure of the tour, full invoiced amount will be charged.</li>
	<li>
		Late Booking inquiry less the 60 days of departure date will be required to do full payment.</li>
	<li>
		All cancellation is required to be informed by written document (e-mail )</li>
</ul>		  </div>

<script>

	  // When the document loads do everything inside here ...
	  $(document).ready(function(){

		// When a link is clicked
		$("a.tab").click(function () {


			// switch all tabs off
			$(".current").removeClass("current");

			// switch this tab on
			$(this).addClass("current");

			// slide all content up
			$(".content_text").slideUp();

			// slide this content up
			var content_show = $(this).attr("name");
			$("#"+content_show).slideDown();

		});

	  });
  </script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#tourcharge').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
   $.ajax({
   type: "POST",
   url: "submitliveboardenquiry.php",
   data: str,
   success: function(msg)
   {
		$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings){
		var myList = msg.split("||");	
					$(this).html(myList[0])
					$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						//$('#submitBtn').attr('disabled',true);
						//alert('test');
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
});

}

 });

return false;

}
</script>

    <div class="body_content">
      <div class="resortbox tabbed_area" >
        <h1>Princess Lara</h1>
        <ul>
          		  <li><a  name="idTab1"  class="tab current">Overview</a></li>
		  		  
		  		             <li ><a name="idTab7" class="tab" >Diving Info</a></li>
		 
		  		  		  
		   		  
		   		  
		              
         
          <li><a name="idTab6" class="tab">Schedules</a></li>
		   <li><a name="idTab8" class="tab">Reviews</a></li>
        </ul>

      <br class="spacer" />
	 
		
		


      
	  <div  class="content content_text" id="idTab1">
          <div class="boxcontent">
		  
			  			  <div class="galleryframe"><div class="thumbs1"><a href="manager/uploads/images/726.jpg"  title="Maldives Princess Lara"><img src="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/displayimage.php?image=http://www.maldivestraveller.com/manager/uploads/images/726.jpg&width=271&height=180&color=16a942&quality=100&resizeImage=0&nocache=1" alt="Maldives Princess Lara" /></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/727.jpg"  title="Princess Lara Top Deck"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/728.jpg"  title="Princess Lara Ocean View out door Lounge"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/729.jpg"  title="Maldives Princess Lara"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/730.jpg"  title="Princess Lara Cabin"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/731.jpg"  title="Princess Lara Lounge"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/732.jpg"  title="Cruising Luxury Liveaboard Princess Lara Maldives"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/733.jpg"  title="Princess Lara"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/734.jpg"  title="Princess Lara"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/736.jpg"  title="Ocean Horizon Princess Lara"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/737.jpg"  title="Princess Lara in Maldives deep blue Ocean"></a><a href="manager/uploads/images/738.jpg"  title="Princess Lara at Night"></a></div><p style='text-align:center;'><a href='javascript:void(0)' id='viewgallery'>View Gallery</a></p></div>			  
        
        
		<p>
	Princess Lara one of the luxurios 5 star liveaboard in Maldives with the highest standard service you can receive from a Maldivian Liveaboard.</p>
<p>
	Princess Lara Liveaboard is design with the best craftsmen work and combining with the most modern amenities in a liveaboard of Maldives. Boat is highly user friendly for serious divers and leisure explorer who would love to experience real Maldives by cruising the beautiful atolls of Maldives.</p>
<p>
	The Liveaboard is specialized with modern diving facilities and provides Nitrox onboard as well with highly experienced dive guides in the industry making sure you get the best dive plans and routes for your dive program.</p>
<p>
	Liveaboard Princess Lara comes with 10 rooms of different categories. On the upper deck of the live aboard you can find 3 suites with double bed giving the over view of deep blue ocean horizon. The lower deck have 3 rooms with double beds and 4 rooms with 1 double bed + 1 single bed (twin beds).</p>
<p>
	The Second deck comes with a big lounge and high quality restaurant and out door lounge area at the back of the liveaboard where you can relax and enjoy the ocean breeze and seeing the beautiful blue ocean scenery, cruising the atolls by the small islands with white sandy beaches. The top deck of the liveaboard Princess Lara comes with a large sundeck and a Jacuzzi where you can soak up in the sun and sip a cocktail and spend a great evening. Princess Lara is a liveaboard for a dreamy diving holiday in Maldives in Style .</p>
<p>
	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: normal;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-weight: bold; ">Boat Specification</span></span></p>
<ul boat_.gif="" class="boatfeature" images="" no-repeat="" right="" scroll="" style="" top="">
	<li>
		Type:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Luxury liveaboard</li>
	<li>
		Year Built :</li>
	<li class="feature">
		2009</li>
	<li>
		Hull:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Wooden, Double Deck</li>
	<li>
		Length:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		35.6 meters</li>
	<li>
		Beam:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		10.2 meters</li>
	<li>
		Accommodation:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Maximum 20 passengers (with 4 tripple rooms)</li>
	<li>
		No of Cabins:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		3 double bed cabins, 4 twin bed cabins, 3 suites double bed cabins with sea view , Hot &amp; Cold water, Air conditioning</li>
	<li>
		Main Saloon</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Full Space Dinning Hall / Buffet Style, Our door dinning, Full service Bar</li>
	<li>
		Entertainments:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Hi-Fi, TV, VCR, DVD, Library and Table Games</li>
	<li>
		Engine Power:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		450HP , Cruising Speed 12 knots / hrs</li>
	<li>
		Electricity:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		220 volts A/C, 12/24 volts DC</li>
	<li>
		Diving:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		Medical Oxygen with required Accessories, Dan Oxygen Kit on the Dive Tender, Medical Lockers on Board, Air Compressor main unit type Bauer Marina 320 &amp; Coltri MCH 16 Tropical Plus, 30 Tanks Aluminum 82 cubic ft/12liters, Nitrox</li>
	<li>
		Communication:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		VHF Radios/GPS Chart Plotter/Depth Sounder/Cell Phones/Small fiber speed launch 25 hp to visit Island</li>
	<li>
		Crew On Board:</li>
	<li class="feature">
		10-12 crews on board who are highly Experience on field.</li>
</ul>		  </div>

<script>

	  // When the document loads do everything inside here ...
	  $(document).ready(function(){

		// When a link is clicked
		$("a.tab").click(function () {


			// switch all tabs off
			$(".current").removeClass("current");

			// switch this tab on
			$(this).addClass("current");

			// slide all content up
			$(".content_text").slideUp();

			// slide this content up
			var content_show = $(this).attr("name");
			$("#"+content_show).slideDown();

		});

	  });
  </script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#tourcharge').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
   $.ajax({
   type: "POST",
   url: "submitliveboardenquiry.php",
   data: str,
   success: function(msg)
   {
		$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings){
		var myList = msg.split("||");	
					$(this).html(myList[0])
					$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						//$('#submitBtn').attr('disabled',true);
						//alert('test');
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
});

}

 });

return false;

}
</script>

	<div class="body_content">
      <div class="resortbox" >
        <h1>Maldives Diving Liveaboards</h1>
       <p>The Maldives is one of the renowned top class diving destination. Loved by the dive travelers for its charming natural beauty, the islands are ringed by white sandy beaches leading to turquoise waters and reefs where marine life is rich and diverse.

We provide divers an opportunity to explore Maldives above and below the surface within our Maldives liveaboards tours. The tours are carried with highly experienced dive guides in charge and focusing on the best dive sites possible to do the tour. 

Typically diving in Maldives require a minimum number nights of 7 nights . Gives you a full week to explore 2 to 3 atolls of Maldives liveaboard diving. 

Our Maldives diving Liveaboards vessels comes with hospitable crew, with years of experience in serving divers and tourists, caters to your needs and ensure that you have a wonderful time in the Maldives.</p>
      </div>
      <br class="spacer" />

		  <h3><a href="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/liveboard/lb_id/1">Eagle Ray Liveaboard</a></h3>
		    		  <img src="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/displayimage.php?image=http://www.maldivestraveller.com/manager/uploads/images/750.jpg&width=200&height=185&color=16a942&quality=100&resizeImage=1&nocache=0" style="margin-left:10px;" align="right" /> 
		           <p>Eagle Ray is modern dive liveaboard in Maldives build by wooden. Customize for the divers convenience and for the under water photographers. Eagle Ray is best known for the serious divers who love to explore Maldives. Dive tours are carried by highly experienced staffs and made sure you have a wonderful diving experience in Maldives.</p>

		           <p>The Sting Ray liveaboard in Maldives is one of the most reputed liveaboard running for years without getting old . Sting Ray Liveaboard is built in 2001 specializing diving Market. The boat is well known for its reasonable price and extensive exclusive service provided to the clients who come to dive in Maldives Liveaboard experience</p>

		           <p>An exclusive liveaboard specialized in many years of diving operation in Maldives for ocean lovers. One of the well reputed liveaboard for its steady and quality tours provided . Maavahi Liveaboard is a boat build by local craftsmen and engineers with the modern amenities to set the standard for traveler and adventures who love to scuba dive in Maldives.</p>

		    		  <img src="http://www.maldivestraveller.com/displayimage.php?image=http://www.maldivestraveller.com/manager/uploads/images/695.jpg&width=200&height=185&color=16a942&quality=100&resizeImage=1&nocache=0" style="margin-left:10px;" align="right" /> 
		           <p>Southern cross is one of the finest liveaboard offered in  mid range operated for diving in Maldives. Southern cross can accommodate a maximum of 22 divers. The boat consists of 10 cabins with all modern amenities. All rooms are full air-condition and with en suites. The cabins have comfortable large toilets with separate shower cabins with hot and cold water.</p>

function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#packagecharges').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

function PackageSeasonSubmit() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageseasonenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

</script>

The master bedroom and two guest rooms which are one floor above overlooks a translucent lagoon.  The enclosed garden terraces enfold the two semi-outdoor bathrooms.</p>

function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#packagecharges').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

function PackageSeasonSubmit() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageseasonenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#packagecharges').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

function PackageSeasonSubmit() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageseasonenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

</script>

function chkClick() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

function PackageSeasonSubmit() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageseasonenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

</script>

        <h1>Summer Breaks!</h1>

        <div class="boxcontent"><p>
	In this summer holiday, Maldives Traveller introduces all new packages specially tailor made especially for you. Laze away in the summer sun and adventurein the crystal clear waters of this &nbsp;amazing selection of resorts in the Maldives. Book now to enjoy an unforgettable summer unlike any other in the beautiful island destination: Maldives.</p></div>

    		        <h3>5 Nights Exhilarating Bandos - Jacuzzi Pool Villa & Deluxe Room</h3>
					<div >
												
					<p> <p>The summer skies and the cool blue waters, that’s what is waiting for you at Exhilarating Bandos. With this unique package you could spend 2 nights at the beautiful Jacuzzi Pool Villa and 3 more nights in the deluxe rooms of Bandos. Each special in its own right, the total 5 nights is sure to be one full of amazement and wonder.
</p> 
<p>Bandos Island Resort, one of the first resorts to open in the Maldives has long remained as one of the pioneers in Tourism. A leading resort destination for over 30 years, it is easy to see why. The island of Bandos is a perfect setting for that romantic getaway or those two weeks of bliss away from work. The sense of calm and serenity the island emanates is truly otherworldly. The gentle lull of the sea, the whistling breeze, and the rustling of the palm fronds on the beach will help transcend you from the hurly-burly rigors of daily life. </p>
<p>The rooms offered with this package are also of note. The Deluxe rooms where you would be spending three nights are spacious and inviting. Located at the dazzling white sandy beach, the deluxe rooms offer a wide range of amenities. Designed with traditional attributes infused with modernity evident on the thatched roof above, the deluxe rooms of Bandos is sure to satisfy all of your needs. In addition to the three nights, you would be spending two additional nights in one of the Jacuzzi pool villas of Bandos. A more recent addition to its already impressive collection of rooms, the Jacuzzi pool villas are luxurious modern villa with a private infinity swimming pool and Cabana style sun deck. Located at the edge of the island overlooking the beautiful Indian Ocean, it is a place of luxury and comfort.</p>
<h4>Package Includes : </h4>
<ul class="listing_1">
		<li>
                      Accommodation: 2 Nights at Jacuzzi Pool Villa & 3 Nights at Deluxe Room</li>
		<li>
			 A complimentary daily breakfast 5 night</li>
                <li>
			Speed Boat Transfer return</li>
        </ul>

<h4>Terms And Conditions Apply : </h4>
<ul class="listing_1">
<li>Only applicable to Accomodations Stated </li>
<li>Rates quoted are per room for 5 nights, for 2 pax</li>
<li>Rates are in USD and are inclusive of 10% service charge, 8% goods & services tax, and Maldivian government bed tax (US$8 per person per night).</li>
<li>Book before July 30,2013</li>
</ul>
[*Stay Period : 1 July – 24 August 2013]</p>

								  <li style="clear:left;"><a href="package_season_booking_form.php?pkgSeason=102" rel="facebox"><span >US$ 2966 Stay 5 Nights :- 1-Jul To 24-Aug - Book Now</span></a></li>

    		        <h3>5 Nights Spellbinding Kurumba Island Resort – Pool Villa & Superior Room</h3>
					<div >
												
					<p> <p>Fun in the sun is epitomized in this amazing package. Spend 3 amazing nights at the Superior room of Kurumba Island Resort and 2 more nights in the luxurious pool villas.  Have one of the most perfect holidays and experience Maldives as a whole.
</p> 
<p>Kurumba Maldives is set on a tropical island in the North Male Atoll, conveniently located a brief 10-minute speedboat ride away from the airport and Male, the Maldivian Capital. Dotted with coconut trees that are the island’s namesake, Kurumba was the first private island resort in The Maldives. Lush tropical gardens, white sandy beaches, and a vibrant House Reef are the hallmarks of this classic Maldivian resort.</p>
<p>Stay in some of the most desirable accommodation in all of Maldives. The pool villa where you would be staying for two nights is one of the most revered rooms in the whole of the resort. The spacious Pool villas consist of a large bedroom, sitting room and verandah that lead to adjoining beachfront gardens. A private courtyard features a swimming pool and a Jacuzzi. The peaceful garden also consists of a thatched roof daybed pavilion for relaxation and sunning day bed. Furthermore the superior room where you would spend the remaining three nights are also equally impressive. These roomy accommodations come with either a gorgeous beach-view terrace or private balcony. The bedrooms leads to a bright sizeable bathroom partly open air. Superior rooms are either located on the ground floor or second floor.</p>
<h4>Package Includes : </h4>

    		        <h3>5 Nights Bewitching Anantara Dhigu – Sunrise Beach Villa & Sunset Pool Villa</h3>
					<div >
												
					<p> <p>If you love excitement and fun in the sun, then the package of bewitching Anantara Dhigu is the perfect choice for you. Surrounded by the clear crystal waters of the Indian Ocean, it is the perfect holiday destination for water sports enthusiasts, couples and even for relaxation. A holiday which you would not forget awaits you. Spend two nights at the wonderful sunrise beach villa and a further three nights at the magnificent sunset pool villa.
</p> 
<p>The Anantara Dhigu resort & Spa located in the South Male’ Atoll has some of the most luxurious and comfortable accommodations available in the Maldives. Just a short 25 minute speedboat ride away, the island is a tropical paradise set that compromises of fascinating natural wonders. Surrounded by crystal clear waters and beautiful white sandy beaches the island is a paradise waiting for you to visit. It is also well equipped for all types of travellers, from families looking to create memories to couples looking for a romantic getaway. </p>
<pThe Sunrise Beach Villa where you would stay for two magical nights are positioned perfectly to view awe inspiring sun rises from the horizon. With luxurious space available, the rooms consist of an outdoor rain shower and a large terrazzo tub in an open air bathroom. The room is also fitted with all of the necessary modern amenities such as a mini bar, flat screen TV and iPod docks. A private terrace with sun loungers and dining areas are also available for quiet relaxing moments to reflect on the beauty surrounding you. The Sunset Pool Villa where you would be spending a further three nights at is also unique and brilliant in its own right. These 162 square meter villas are set on the primes luxury beach of Dhigu Maldives. Relax on your own stretch of the beach or cool down in the villa’s private plunge pool set in the rear garden available in this amazing room. Designed to provide the utmost experience of a Maldivian Resort it is a room that would not disappoint.</p>
<h4>Package Includes : </h4>

    		        <h3>5 Nights Ravishing Vellassaru Maldives: Villa with Pool & Deluxe Bungalow</h3>
					<div >
												
					<p> <p>Tailor made with the intention of providing the best holiday experience kept in mind, the Ravishing Vellassaru is sure to provide you the best summer holiday vacation. Whether your vice is snorkeling in the brilliant waters surrounding the island, water sports activities or just relaxing on the beach, Vellasaru Maldives would not disappoint.
</p> 
<p>Journey to the secluded island retreat of Velassaru Maldives. This distinct Maldives Island hotel inspired by local architecture features minimalism with chic simplicity. All rooms feature high vaulted ceiling and panoramic walls invoking a sense of space and providing its guest with elegance. Have all your impulses answered with the best services provided to make your stay comfortable. </p>
<p>Spend three amazing nights at the deluxe bungalows of Vellassaru. Located at the powdery white sanded beach these split level bedrooms consists of an open terrace with a day. The interiors are designed to be both spacious and warm with the use of teak and tropical foliage that blends in seamlessly. The adjoining garden bathroom with a shower refreshes and revitalizes you. The Pool villa of Velassaru where you would be spending the remaining two nights are best described as luxurious and mesmerizing. These secluded compounds have a sprawling veranda and a spacious en suite bathroom. An oversized lap pool with a poolside gazebo and dining area adds to your luxury.</p>

var _gaq = _gaq || [];

<script type="text/javascript">
function updateTotalPrice(guest)
{
	var enqTotal=($('#packagecharges').val()*guest).toFixed(2);
	$('#enqguest').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqguest').html(guest);$('#enqguest').fadeIn('slow');});			
	$('#enqtotal').fadeOut('slow',function() {$('#enqtotal').html(enqTotal);$('#enqtotal').fadeIn('slow');});			
}
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
function chkClick() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

function PackageSeasonSubmit() 
{
		var str = $('#contactform').serialize();
		$.ajax({
		type: "POST",
		url: "submitpackageseasonenquiry.php",
		data: str,
		success: function(msg)
		{
			$("#error").ajaxComplete(function(event, request, settings)
			{
				var myList = msg.split("||");	
				$(this).html(myList[0])
				$(this).fadeIn('slow');
					if (myList[1]=="1")
					{
						$('#contactform').clearForm();
					}
				});
			}
		});
return false;
}

</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>

<script>jQuery(document).ready(function($)
{

    $('#txtStartDate, #txtEndDate').datepicker(
    {
        //showOn: "both",
        beforeShow: customRange,
        dateFormat: "yy-mm-dd",
        firstDay: 1, 
        changeFirstDay: false
    });

});

function customRange(input) 
{ 
   		//var min = new Date(2008, 11 - 1, 1); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
		var min = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute minimum date
        var dateMin = min;
        var dateMax = null;
		//var dateMax = new Date(2011, 11 - 1, 1); 
        var dayRange = 30;  // Set this to the range of days you want to restrict to
    
        
        if (input.id == "txtStartDate") 
        {
		
            if ($("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate") != null)
            {
                //dateMax = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin = $("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
				//min=$("#txtEndDate").datepicker("getDate");
                //dateMin.setDate(dateMin.getDate() - dayRange);
                //if (dateMin < min)
                {
                //        dateMin = min;
                }
             }
             else
             {
                //dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
				//dateMax = new Date(); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
             }                      
        }
        else if (input.id == "txtEndDate")
        {
                dateMax = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate"); //Set this to your absolute maximum date
                if ($("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate") != null) 
                {
                        dateMin = $("#txtStartDate").datepicker("getDate");
						//dateMin = new Date(dateMin + 4);
						dateMin = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + 1);
                        var rangeMax = new Date(dateMin.getFullYear(), dateMin.getMonth(), dateMin.getDate() + dayRange);

                        if(rangeMax > dateMax)
                        {
                            dateMax = rangeMax; 
                        }
                }
        }
    return {
                minDate: dateMin, 
                maxDate: dateMax
            }; 

}
</script>
